            ]
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "uuid": "blog-002-typescript-tips",
            "title": "10 TypeScript Tips That Will Make You a Better Developer",
            "slug": "typescript-tips-better-developer",
            "content": "<p>TypeScript has become essential for building maintainable JavaScript applications. Here are 10 tips I've learned that will level up your TypeScript skills.</p><h2>1. Use 'unknown' Instead of 'any'</h2><p>When you don't know the type, prefer 'unknown' over 'any'. It's type-safe and forces you to narrow the type before using it.</p><h2>2. Leverage Discriminated Unions</h2><p>Create powerful type-safe patterns with discriminated unions...</p><h2>3. Template Literal Types</h2><p>TypeScript 4.1 introduced template literal types that enable amazing string manipulation at the type level...</p>",
